        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Disovizija is an annual event hosted by the Čačak City Library to promote poetry among youth. In this year&rsquo;s event, I was given the opportunity to read one of my works to live audience for the very first time.</p>
<figure class="float-left"><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nicolasGreenwood/Images/refs/heads/main/nicolaspoetryrecital.jpg"
    alt="Greenwood reciting poetry at Disovizija, 2025"><figcaption>
      <p>Photo courtesy of Čačak City Library Vladislav Petković Dis</p>
    </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Reading poetry out loud is an entirely different experience to reading to yourself. Poetic language isn&rsquo;t always rational and predictable, and there&rsquo;s something about hearing it out loud that makes you slow down a little, hang on longer to each word and appreciate its artistic courage even more.</p>]]></summary>
